## ğŸ“Œ Fraud Detection Logic

### **1ï¸âƒ£ What is "Time"?**
- `"Time"` represents **seconds since the first recorded transaction.**  
- High `"Time"` differences can help detect unusual transaction patterns.

### **2ï¸âƒ£ How Does the Model Work?**
- The ML model analyzes **transaction amount & timing patterns**  
- It uses **Anomaly Detection** (e.g., Isolation Forest) to detect fraud  
- If fraud is detected, an **email alert** is sent  

### **3ï¸âƒ£ How are Fraud Transactions Identified?**
| Time (Seconds) | Amount ($) | Fraudulent? |
|---------------|------------|------------|
| 500          | 20         | âŒ No |
| 30000        | 5000       | âœ… Yes |
| 50000        | 30         | âŒ No |
| 86400        | 7000       | âœ… Yes |

